This is the Definitive Project Structure for Paradox OS.
This structure mimics a professional kernel environment (like Linux or BSD) but is streamlined for a modern "from scratch" build using Limine (Bootloader) and GCC (Compiler).
Create a root folder named paradox-os and create exactly these subfolders and files inside it.
ğŸ“‚ Root Directory: paradox-os/
This is your workspace.
File / Folder	Purpose
ğŸ“ build/	Stores the compiled ISO image (paradox.iso).
ğŸ“ objs/	Stores temporary .o files (keeps source folders clean).
ğŸ“ limine/	Contains the Limine bootloader binary and headers.
ğŸ“ src/	The Source Code. (See below for details).
ğŸ“ assets/	Fonts, Icons, Wallpapers, and Bitmaps.
ğŸ“„ Makefile	The automation script to compile everything.
ğŸ“„ linker.ld	The map telling the CPU where to put code in RAM.
ğŸ“„ limine.cfg	Configuration file for the boot menu.
ğŸ“‚ The Source Directory: src/
This is where the magic happens. We separate Interface (Header files) from Implementation (C files).
1. src/include/ (The Blueprints)
Header files (.h) go here. This defines how different parts of the OS talk to each other.
